        <div class="main-con w-full">
            <div class="sub-con w-11/12 m-auto">

                <!-- ///////// isse repeat krna h h1,p img tag-->
                <h1 class="text-lg font-bold mt-5 mb-2">Edit Profile and Manage Lecture</h1>
                <p>Faculty users can edit their profile (first name, last name or even can add their phone number if
                    they want) and add their lectures or even remove them.</p>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 1:</h4>
                <p>Go to the 'Manage Profile and Edit Lecture' button present in Profile page.</p>
                <img src="images/managepimg1.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 2:</h4>
                <p>You'll see all the data that's already present in your profile. If needed then you can edit your
                    first name or last name or phone number, and then click on 'Save Changes' button to save those
                    changes. </p>
                <img src="images/managepimg2.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 3:</h4>
                <p>After saving changes, if you want to go back to Faculty Dashboard then choose 'Dashboard' option but
                    if you want to further manage your lectures then click for 'Manage Lecture' button (as highlighted).
                </p>
                <img src="images/managepimg3.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 4:</h4>
                <p>Now to Add lecture, select the Year, Semester, Section and Subject name from the drop down.</p>
                <img src="images/editlimg1.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5"> <br>
                <p>After that, click on 'Add Lecture' button and your lecture will be saved!</p>
                <img src="images/editlimg2.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 5:</h4>
                <p>View all your available lectures by clicking on the'Show Lecture' button. (This data is now saved and
                    won't be displayed for other faculty IDs. This is done to prevent having more than one faculty with
                    same lecture.) <br>
                    You may delete a particular lecture by clicking on the respective cross-button and that lecture will
                    be removed.</p>
                <img src="images/editlimg3.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5"> <br>
                <p>To go back to Editing Profile, choose this highlighted 'Edit Profile' button or simply Select for
                    'Dashboard' to return to your Dashboard.</p>
                <br>    

                <!-- ///////////////////////// -->
                <h1 class="text-lg font-bold mt-5 mb-2">Marking Attendance</h1>
                <p>You can mark the attendance of students for a specific lecture from the 'Mark Attendance' page. This
                    data will be recorded for the current date, and the attendance status for students can be edited
                    throughout the 24-hour duration of that date. </p>
                <h5 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 1:</h5>
                <p>Click on 'Mark Attendance' from left menu. <br>Select the desired lecture and click for the'Take
                    Attendance' button.</p>
                <img src="images/markattimg1.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 2:</h4>
                <p>You'll see the list of students that are taking those lectures. Now you can mark them as present or
                    absent by clicking (or unclicking) respective checkboxes.</p>
                <img src="images/markattimg2.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <img src="images/markattimg3.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <br>
                <p> Click the 'Mark All Present' button to mark all students as present, and click the 'Mark All Absent'
                    button to mark all students as absent while still recording the attendance date.</p>
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Step 3:</h4>
                <p>Scroll down to the 'Save' button to save attendance for all students of this lecture along with the
                    date the attendance is marked. <br>
                    Note: If you choose to simply click the 'Save' button for a list of students without checking any
                    boxes, attendance for all students will be recorded as Absent for that specific lecture and date by
                    default.</p>
                <img src="images/markattimg4.png" class="w-4/5 m-auto mt-5">
                <br>
                
                <!-- ///////////////////////// -->
                <h1 class="text-lg font-bold mt-5 mb-2">View Attendance</h1>
                <p>You can view the attendance of students for a specific lecture from the 'Mark Attendance' page. kjlkfs</p>



